Default and static methods on interfaces.

Since Java eight, interfaces can carry concrete methods too. A default method is a method on the interface that has a body. Every implementing class inherits this default method for free, but the implementer is allowed to override it if they want. The keyword default goes before the return type. A static method on an interface is a utility method that belongs to the interface itself. You call it as Greeter dot friendly, not on an instance.

Default methods are how the java util Collection and Stream application programming interfaces were extended in Java eight without breaking every existing implementation. They are also why an interface with a single abstract method, sometimes called a functional interface, can be implemented by a lambda. You will see plenty of that pattern in notebook four.
